title: UFC Coming To Channel 10 & Paramount+ In 2026 | 10 News
description: The biggest fighting competition in the world has a new home: Paramount+ and Channel 10 will be the new home of UFC in Australia in 2026.  All UFC Fight Nights and the prelims for marquee numbered UFC events will be broadcast live on Paramount+ in Australia, as well as select live UFC events free-to-air on Channel 10.  The deal is an extension of the international UFC partnership signed with Paramount+ in the US earlier this year, and begins from January 1, 2026. title: Hurricane Melissa Weakens To Category 4 After Devastating Jamaica, Heads Towards Cuba | 10 News
description: Hurricane Melissa has weakened to a Category 4 system with sustained winds of 233kph as its eyewall moves off Jamaica’s northern coast, according to the latest National Hurricane Centre update.  The storm made landfall earlier Tuesday in Jamaica’s southwest with winds of up to 297kph, tearing apart homes, toppling trees and powerlines, and triggering widespread flooding and landslides.  Authorities say much of the island remains without power or communication, with entire communities cut off by blocked roads and debris.  Melissa is expected to make a second landfall in eastern Cuba late Tuesday or early Wednesday, still bringing life-threatening storm surge and damaging winds. title: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu Orders ‘Powerful’ Strikes On Gaza | 10 News
description: Israel has launched strikes on Gaza on Tuesday night after Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu ordered the military to immediately carry out "powerful" attacks in the Palestinian territory.  It comes after Netanyahu accused Hamas of violating the two-week-old ceasefire agreement and staging the discovery of a deceased hostage.  At least eight people were killed in the strikes, including three in Gaza City's Sabra neighborhood and five in a car targeted in Khan Younis. title: Alleged Drug Strikes Kill 14 In Pacific Ocean | 10 News
description: The US military has once again come under scrutiny after launching strikes on four suspected drug-smuggling boats in the eastern Pacific, killing 14 people and leaving one survivor.   Defence Secretary Pete Hegseth said the vessels were linked to “designated terrorist organisations,” but legal experts have questioned the basis for using lethal force outside of war zones.   The Trump administration reportedly approved a classified opinion allowing traffickers to be treated as enemy combatants, a move critics say bypasses judicial oversight and international law.   Mexican authorities have taken charge of rescuing the survivor after being informed by Washington.   It’s the latest in a growing series of strikes raising ethical and legal concerns about the US’s expanding anti-narcotics campaign. title: Shark Feeding Frenzy Off Gold Coast's Snapper Rocks | 10 News
description: A spectacular but dangerous natural phenomenon has been caught on camera after a school of bait fish triggered a feeding frenzy at a popular Gold Coast surfing beach yesterday.  Videos posted to social media show a pack of sharks thrashing their fins and tails around in the shallows, attacking a bait ball right on the edge of the sand at Snapper Rocks.  It’s understood the swell has increased and all the bait has moved offshore, with no shark’s sighted since.  The beaches have re-opened, and lifeguards will continue to monitor the waters. title: Hurricane Melissa Dubbed ‘Storm Of The Century’ Heads Towards Cuba | 10 News
description: Hurricane Melissa is being described as ‘the storm of the century’ in fact, no Atlantic Hurricane stronger than Melissa has ever made landfall.   The system lashed Jamaica with record winds of almost 300 kilometres an hour.  It's since been downgraded but it was a category five hurricane and brought heavy rain and catastrophic flooding to much of the small island nation leaving many of the 2.8 million residents stranded and without power.  US Correspondent Katherine Firkin has the latest. title: Australian Company's Groundbreaking Laser Weapon To Fight Drones | 10 News+
description: Australian defence company Electro Optics Systems has developed a groundbreaking new laser weapon called Apollo, which can shoot down drones on the battlefield with a beam of light. title: Australian Astronomers Capture New Image Of Milky Way | 10 News
description: It's the Milky Way like you've never seen it before.  Hailed as a milestone, Australian astronomers have released a spectacular new image of the galaxy home to our solar system.  The photograph, showing the expansive galactic plane, took 18 months to construct and is the largest low-frequency radio colour image of the Milky Way.
